来吧  颠簸一路你一定想洗澡
Come, you'll be wanting a bath after all that travel.

74
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:03,470
还要换一件正餐穿的裙子
Oh, and a dress for dinner.

75
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:04,990
你可以穿我的
You can wear one of mine.

76
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,760
你喜欢什么颜色
What's your color?

77
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:09,780
午夜蓝还是银色
Midnight blue or silver?

78
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:12,120
或许银色  快来
Silver, maybe. Come.

79
00:10:12,510 --> 00:10:14,690
你愿意话可以在我的房间里选一间住
You can choose one of my bedrooms if you want.

80
00:10:23,670 --> 00:10:25,050
没有别的办法吗
Is there no other way?

81
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:27,480
你怕她有危险
You're afraid for her?

82
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:30,120
我当然怕
Of course I'm afraid for her!

83
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:36,600
看起来就很危险
It just seems very dangerous.

84
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,940
她会受到保护的
She'll be protected the entire way.

85
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,790
战士之子对越界之人
The Faith Militant are very stern

86
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:44,240
绝不容情
with those who overstep their bounds.

87
00:10:46,420 --> 00:10:50,050
况且玛格丽王后不是你母亲
And Queen Margaery isn't your mother.

88
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:52,950
我想诸神也会为她
I suspect the gods will predispose the common people

89
00:10:52,950 --> 00:10:55,160
让平民温和起来
to gentleness on her behalf.

90
00:10:55,370 --> 00:10:57,830
她真正对他们敞开过心扉
She's truly opened her heart to them.

91
00:10:58,620 --> 00:11:02,150
她一直都热衷帮助穷苦和不幸的平民
She's always been very devoted to the poor and the unfortunate.

92
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:04,930
对七神也诚心信奉
And now she's devoted to the gods as well.

93
00:11:07,610 --> 00:11:09,070
你想见她吗
Would you like to see her?

94
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:32,570
他们有伤害你吗
Have they hurt you?

95
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:34,270
他们有对你不好吗
Have they mistreated you?

96
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:37,120
-没有  陛下  -我好想你
- No, Your Grace. - I've missed you.

97
00:11:37,590 --> 00:11:39,240
你都不知道我多想你
More than you could know.

98
00:11:39,430 --> 00:11:41,380
我们很快就能团聚了
We'll be together again soon

99
00:11:41,510 --> 00:11:44,230
一切都会比从前好
and everything will be better than it was before.

100
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,800
怎么会好
Better how?

101
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:47,440
很快就有...
Soon the--

102
00:11:50,420 --> 00:11:51,730
赎罪之旅
walk of atonement.

103
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:54,830
他说没有别的办法
He says there's no other way.

104
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:58,760
你跟大麻雀谈过吗
Have you spoken to him at all, the High Sparrow?

105
00:11:59,070 --> 00:12:01,650
是的  谈过几次
Yes, a few times.

106
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:04,000
你呢
Have you?

107
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,170
谈过
Yes, I have.

108
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:07,790
他跟我们想的不太一样  是吧
He's not quite what we thought he was, is he?

109
00:12:11,070 --> 00:12:12,200
你觉得我疯了
You think I'm mad.

110
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,420
我听上去像是疯了
I sound mad.

111
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,520
不  没有
No. No, you don't.

112
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:18,610
你绝不会的
You-- you could never.

113
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:20,350
你说得对  他是跟我们想的不一样
You're right, he's not.

114
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:21,890
他要更...
He's a lot more--

115
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:23,240
是的
He is.

116
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:25,720
他很特别
There's something about him.

117
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:27,950
他看待这世界的方式
His way of looking at the world.

118
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:34,970
承认真实的自己并不容易
It's not an easy thing admitting to yourself what you really are.

119
00:12:35,890 --> 00:12:37,440
我花了好久才肯面对
It's taken me a while.

120
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:39,400
他帮助了我
He's helped me.

121
00:12:40,770 --> 00:12:42,180
你在说什么呢
What are you talking about?

122
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:46,510
你是个好人  你一直是个好人
You're a good person. You've always been a good person.

123
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:49,330
你是我认识的最好的人
You're the best person I know. 

124
00:12:49,980 --> 00:12:52,430
我刚刚还跟他谈起你对穷人的奉献
I was just telling him about your devotion to the poor.

125
00:12:52,430 --> 00:12:54,590
是啊  我去他们的茅舍
Ah, yes, I visited their hovels

126
00:12:54,590 --> 00:12:58,130
我给他们汤喝  而且确保让人看到
and I fed them soup and I made sure I was seen doing it.

127
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:02,350
但他们真正需要的我没有给他们
I never gave them what they really needed, though.

128
00:13:03,460 --> 00:13:07,900
我有很多时间去思考我多么擅长假仁假义
I've had lots of time to think about how good I was at seeming good.

129
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:11,870
我对自己的本质  行善的动机
All those stories I told myself about who I was

130
00:13:11,870 --> 00:13:14,480
充满了自欺欺人的想法
and why I did the things I did.

131
00:13:15,730 --> 00:13:18,870
其中有太多谎言
There were so many lies in those stories.

132
00:13:20,510 --> 00:13:21,860
我不懂
I don't understand.

133
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:24,040
没关系  真的
It's all right. It really is.

134
00:13:24,930 --> 00:13:27,940
放下那些谎言让我如释重负
It's such a relief to let go of those lies.

135
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,450
那洛拉斯呢
What about Loras?

136
00:13:37,180 --> 00:13:38,640
我爱我哥哥
I love my brother.

137
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,880
我会永远爱我哥哥
I will always love my brother.

138
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:46,690
他的灵魂是纯粹而完美的
His soul is pure and perfect.

139
00:13:47,390 --> 00:13:49,230
他的罪孽并不能抹去那份纯洁
His sins don't erase that purity,

140
00:13:49,230 --> 00:13:51,110
只是遮掩了它
they only obscure it.

141
00:13:51,810 --> 00:13:56,020
他只需要赎罪
He just needs to atone for them.

142
00:13:57,260 --> 00:13:58,550
我们都得赎罪
We all do.

143
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:01,510
不论如何  或迟或早
Sooner or later, one way or another.

144
00:14:03,110 --> 00:14:05,980
诸神对我们所有人都有计划
The gods have a plan for us all.

145
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:23,880
穿这个走路真不舒服
It's hard to walk in this.

146
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:27,990
真美
It's beautiful.

147
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:32,060
你真美
You're beautiful.

148
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,950
这鹿肉  很好吃
This venison, it's very tasty.

149
00:15:23,730 --> 00:15:25,260
是今天打来的吗
Is it from today's hunt?

150
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,760
不是
Well, no.

151
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,460
那只还没处理完呢
We haven't been able to cure that one yet.

152
00:15:30,060 --> 00:15:31,400
这只是上周的
This is last week's.

153
00:15:32,630 --> 00:15:34,610
当然了  抱歉
Oh, of course. Sorry.

154
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:36,870
路途劳顿
Long journey.

155
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:40,000
在七十码开外射倒了它
Brought it down from 70 yards.

156
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,150
一击致命
One shot.

157
00:15:42,170 --> 00:15:45,220
好远啊
Oh, that's a fair distance.

158
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:48,500
你在长城也常打猎吗
So do you do much hunting up at the Wall?

159
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:50,590
是的  当然
Oh, yes. Yes.

160
00:15:51,670 --> 00:15:52,920
常打呢
A good amount.

161
00:15:53,950 --> 00:15:55,420
在长城以北
North of the Wall,

162
00:15:55,630 --> 00:15:57,590
不打猎就没得吃
you don't hunt, you don't eat.

163
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:01,310
一般是猎鹿还是跟我们一样猎麋鹿
Mostly deer or is it elk as well?

164
00:16:02,970 --> 00:16:04,130
兔子
Rabbits.

165
00:16:05,470 --> 00:16:07,230
有时候猎松鼠
Sometimes squirrels.

166
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:14,270
"我们"主要是指我朋友琼恩
I say "We," It's my friend Jon mostly.

167
00:16:14,830 --> 00:16:16,330
有时还有艾迪
Sometimes Edd.

168
00:16:16,980 --> 00:16:18,230
还有吉莉
Oh, and Gilly.

169
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:21,180
她也是个好猎手
She's-- she's quite a good hunter as well.

170
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:23,560
女猎手
Um, huntress.

171
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:26,670
这在你们那里是常事吧
I imagine it's common where you're from.

172
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:28,190
我们遇到过一个人
We once met a man,

173
00:16:28,190 --> 00:16:30,620
最后壁炉城的安柏大人  对吧  蓝道
Lord Umber from Last Hearth, wasn't it, Randyll,

174
00:16:30,780 --> 00:16:33,010
说他的女儿都要学打猎
who said he taught all his daughters how to hunt.

175
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:35,120
你父亲教你打猎吗
Your father taught you to hunt?

176
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:37,790
我们的父亲是绝不会教我们的
Our father would never teach us.

177
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:41,110
我们的父亲大概能跟你父亲学学
I think our father could learn a thing or two from your father.

178
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:42,800
够了
That's enough of that.

179
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:47,940
山姆威尔  你还想再来点面包吗
Samwell, would you care for more bread?

180
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:50,750
好  当然
Yes. Yes, please.

181
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:51,890
谢谢  妈妈
Thank you, Mother.

182
00:16:56,780 --> 00:16:58,360
还不够胖吗
Not fat enough already?

183
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:13,480
我是依总司令的命令南下
I travelled south under orders from the Lord Commander.

184
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:15,560
-他要我...  -我读过你的信
- He wants me to-- - I read your letter.

185
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:19,950
你要做个学士
You're to be a maester.

186
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:23,100
是的  等我拿到了项链
Yes. And once I have my chain,

187
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:25,560
我就回黑城堡
I'll return to Castle Black.

188
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:28,570
我以为守夜人能让你历练成男人
I thought the Night's Watch might make a man of you.

189
00:17:30,590 --> 00:17:32,550
至少有点男人样
Something resembling a man at least.

190
00:17:33,920 --> 00:17:37,570
你还是那么软弱  肥胖
You managed to stay soft and fat.

191
